<h5 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h5>
<p>Consider the following "trick",</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\int\sec(x)\dx{x}=\int\sec(x)\frac{\sec(x)+\tan(x){}}{\tan(x)+\sec(x){}}\dx{x}=\int\frac{\sec^2(x)+\sec(x)\tan(x)}{\tan(x)+\sec(x)}\dx{x}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">Do you recognize a substitution that can be used?  Use this to integrate <span class="process-math">\(\sec(x)\dx{x}{}\text{.}\)</span></p>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-4.html#p-89" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
</body>
